Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Police are requesting assistance in solving a murder case in Tafelsig.On Sunday 18 September at 19:00 Mitchell s Plain police received a complaint of a shooting in Guava Street. On arrival police were taken to the kitchen where a 36-year-old woman was lying on the floor with a gunshot wound to her chest. She was declared dead at the scene. It is alleged the deceased had been standing outside in the road when shots were fired between two groups in the street. She had felt a pain in her chest and realised that she had been shot, thereafter she ran into the house. No arrest have been made. The motive is currently unknown and police are investigating a case of murder. V Anyone with information on the incident is urged to call the investigating officer Detective Constable Angus November on 082 777 8076. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.